Via ASC PropertyVia GameFeature ActionVia C++ at Runtime <p>On your character's <code>UFWAbilitySystemComponent</code>, add <code>AS_CombatMelee</code> to the Granted Ability Sets array. The set is automatically granted on <code>InitAbilityActorInfo</code>.</p> <p>In your GameFeature plugin's <code>GameFeatureData</code> asset:</p> <ol> <li>Add an action: Add Abilities (FW GAS System).</li> <li>Configure an entry:<ul> <li>Actor Class: Your character class.</li> <li>Granted Ability Sets: <code>AS_CombatMelee</code>.</li> </ul> </li> </ol> <p>When the GameFeature activates, the combat set is granted. When deactivated, it is cleanly removed.</p> <pre><code>void AMyCharacter::GrantCombatAbilities()
{
    UFWAbilitySystemComponent* ASC = FindComponentByClass&lt;UFWAbilitySystemComponent&gt;();
    if (!ASC) return;

    // Load the AbilitySet
    UFWAbilitySet* CombatSet = LoadObject&lt;UFWAbilitySet&gt;(
        nullptr, TEXT("/Game/Data/AbilitySets/AS_CombatMelee.AS_CombatMelee"));

    if (CombatSet)
    {
        FFWAbilitySetHandle Handle;
        ASC-&gt;GiveAbilitySet(CombatSet, Handle);

        // Store handle to remove later if needed
        CombatSetHandle = Handle;
    }
}
</code></pre>

